		<div id="comment_body_64373740"><p><div class="quote"><p>At least they didn't blame the layoffs on AI, like many other co's did. Tech is simply in a slump, just like 83, 92, and 2002.</p></div><p>I mean, it's not like anybody didn't see this coming.  They've been working on this project for an entire decade, and despite several leadership changes, they still didn't have a shippable project.  Sometimes, you try something and it just does't work, and at some point, you have to cut your losses.  I don't think anyone should fault Tim Cook for that.</p><p>Killing failing projects is <b>very</b> different from cutting a bunch of random people scattered throughout the company just to lower headcount numbers without any<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64373740">

